author: jsonline
title: Prep Roundup - Arrowhead churns out victory
text:
Arrowhead brought it's A-game Saturday.
The state's top-ranked Division 1 girls swim team, paced by a victory from its 200-yard medley relay to start the meet and a win later in day by senior Rocky Laabs in the 500 Afreestyle, won the title at the Highlander Invite at Homestead with 331.5 points. Second-place Verona-Mount Horeb had 283 points.
Arrowhead set the tone by winning the meet's first event. The team of sophomore Holly Stoll, senior Taylor Stoll, sophomore Abby Cabush and junior Alyssa Lewandowski won in 1 minute, 50.50 seconds. Laab won the 500 free, the seventh event of the day, in 5:05.61.
Arrowhead also got second-place finishes from Cabush in the 200 free (1:54.09), Holly Stoll in the 200 individual medley (2:11.54) and the 200 free relay of senior Kelly Jacob, Lewandowski, Laabs and Taylor Stoll in 1:40.23.
Cedarburg senior Katie Drabot won the 100 free in 50.77, the 200 free in 1:53.55 and anchored the 400 free relay to victory in 3:33.12.
Watertown Invite: Senior Meredith Huber won the 50 free and 100 free and was a part of victorious 200 free and 400 free relays to lead Hartford to the team title. The Orioles had 520 points, 94 more than second-place Greenfield/Pius XI.
Katie Hayes, a freshman from Brown Deer/University School, won three events. She opened the meet by anchoring the 200 medley relay to victory and then won the 200 individual medley and 100 breaststroke.
FOOTBALL Milwaukee North 36, Milwaukee Reagan 32: The Blue Devils scored the game-winning points on a 20-yard pass from Chris Pickens to Deangelo Pompey with 1 second left. Pompey had four touchdowns.
CROSS COUNTRY Shorewood Invitational: Shorewood senior Morgan Florsheim won the 5,000-meter race at Kern Park in 19:20.12 to lead her team to the title. Kenosha Bradford was the boys winner.
Mark Stewart
